-- Dubai says world's tallest tower is 2,717 feet high
-- 
-- Mon Jan 4, 2010 11:38am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/01/04/us-dubai-burj-height-idUSTRE60330D20100104

 

 DUBAI  (Reuters) - Dubai opened the world's tallest structure on Monday, and a statement said it was 828 meters (2,717 ft) high. 

 Dubai's ruler Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid al-Maktoum renamed the tower Burj Khalifa after the president of the United Arab Emirates and the ruler of the neighboring emirate of Abu Dhabi. (Reporting by Tom Atkins; Writing by Firouz Sedarat)